  "local_port": 54580,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best pancake recipe that doesn't use baking powder?",
  "response": "If you're out of baking powder or prefer not to use it, you can still make delicious pancakes using this simple recipe. Instead of baking powder, this recipe relies on the natural lift from whipped egg whites to ensure the pancakes are light and fluffy.\n\n### Ingredients:\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup milk\n- 2 large eggs, separated\n- 2 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional, for added flavor)\n\n### Instructions:\n1. **Prepare the Dry Ingredients:**\n   - In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, and salt until well combined.\n\n2. **Mix the Wet Ingredients:**\n   - In a separate bowl, whisk the egg yolks. Add the milk, melted butter, and vanilla extract. Stir until the mixture is smooth.\n\n3. **Combine the Mixtures:**\n   - Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in the wet mixture. Stir gently with a spatula until just combined. Be careful not to overmix; it's okay if the batter has a few small lumps.\n\n4. **Whip the Egg Whites:**\n   - In a clean, dry bowl, whip the egg whites using a hand mixer or whisk until stiff peaks form. This might take a few minutes with a whisk but is essential for fluffy pancakes.\n\n5. **Fold in the Egg Whites:**\n   - Gently fold the whipped egg whites into the batter using a spatula. Be careful to retain as much air as possible for light, airy pancakes.\n\n6. **Cook the Pancakes:**\n   - Preheat a non-stick griddle or frying pan over medium heat. Lightly grease with butter or oil.\n   - Pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the griddle for each pancake. Cook until the surface has formed bubbles and the edges look set, about 2-3 minutes.\n   - Flip the pancakes and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes on the other side until golden brown.\n\n7. **Serve:**\n   - Remove from the pan and keep warm in a low oven if making multiple batches. Serve with your favorite toppings like maple syrup, fresh fruits, or a sprinkle of powdered sugar.\n\nEnjoy your homemade pancakes without baking powder!",
